{Speech 11}{}{How can't you know how to play poker? It's POKER!\nOkay, listen here. The aim is to get best hand than your opponents have.}
{Speech 11 Answer 12}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 12}{}{Here are all the possible hands:\nOne pair (two cards of the same rank, two Kings for example).\nTwo pairs (two cards of the same rank plus two of another that match each other, two Jacks and two Sevens for example),\nThree of a kind (three cards of the same rank).}
{Speech 12 Answer 13}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 13}{}{Straight (five cards of sequential rank, but in more than one suit; 7S, 8H, 9S, 10D and JC).\nFlush (five cards of the same suit).\nFull House (three of a kind and one pair).}
{Speech 13 Answer 14}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 14}{}{Four of a kind (four cards of the same rank).\nStraight flush (five cards in sequence, all of the same suit).\nRoyal Flush (Ace Straight flush).}
{Speech 14 Answer 15}{}{[Далее]}
{Speech 15}{}{These are all the hands. Not too difficult, eh?}
{Speech 15 Answer 16}{}{[Далее]}
{Speech 16}{}{If several players have the best hands in the end, the one who has higher kicker wins.}
{Speech 16 Answer 17}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 17}{}{Players are dealt five cards face down, and then the first round of betting begins.\nBetting lasts until every player calls the bet or everyone folds.\nAfter that each player can trade his cards in the hand for cards from the deck.}
{Speech 17 Answer 18}{}{[Далее]}
{Speech 18}{}{After trading the second round of betting takes place. After that players show their hands.\nPot is divided between winners, but commonly only one wins.\nWell, that's it. Will you play?}
{Speech 18 Answer 2}{}{Hmm, Ok.}
{Speech 18 Answer Exit}{}{Not now. [Leave]}
